http://allafrica.com/stories/201611030775.html
[As part of government's health sector reform, President Ernest Bai Koroma on Wed [2 Nov 2016] turned the sod for the construction of 3 ultra-modern tertiary hospitals in the Western Area, including Waterloo, Lumley and Bambara Town.
The project is funded by the Kuwaiti Government in collaboration with the Government of Sierra Leone.]

[These hospitals should serve the country well. One hopes they have appropriate training for healthcare workers and facilities for Ebola patients should the disease reemerge. - Mod.LK]

